{
  "doc_id": "52077",
  "text": "Today's virtual worlds and massively multiplayer online role-playing games (MMORPGs) are descendants of Multiuser virtual environments (MUVEs) [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] of the 1980s. Current examples, such as Second Life (secondlife.com) or World of Warcraft (us.blizzard.com) appear to have a strong appeal on users [CITATION_3] , [CITATION_4] and seem to enhance participant involvement when used for educational and training purposes [CITATION_5] . A comprehensive presentation of virtual worlds, their history and availability to date is beyond the scope of this paper; the reader can obtain such information from other sources such as Bartle [CITATION_6] and Duncann et al. [CITATION_7] . Instead, we focus on the most prominent examples, employed in education and training.",
